Thus they who are possessed by desire suffer much and enjoy little, as the ox
that drags a cart gets but a morsel of grass. For the sake of this morsel of
enjoyment, which falls easily to the beastâ€™s lot. man, blinded by his
destiny, wastes this brief fortune, that is so hard to win.
